          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Protecting Families and Small Businesses Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act to allow a health insurer to reduce&nbsp;its 2018 annual&nbsp;fee by the amount of premium rebates provided to enrollees under this bill. Premium rebates must be equal to the lesser of 2% of the net premiums for each individual or the premiums paid by an individual.</p><p>For a Medicaid managed care organization, the 2018 annual fee shall be reduced by 2% of the net premiums.</p> <p>The bill suspends the annual fee for 2019.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
